COOK onion in oil in large nonstick skillet on medium-high heat until tender- crisp and lightly browned, stirring occasionally. ADD all remaining ingredients except sour cream and parsley; mix well. Bring to boil. Reduce heat to medium-low; cover. Simmer 10 to 12 minutes or until noodles are tender. Remove from heat. STIR in sour cream. Sprinkle with parsley.